bilingual.source: The animals here are free and they aren't in cages.
bilingual.target: 这里的动物是自由的，它们不在笼子里。

bilingual.source: As a single, he enjoys a free lifestyle.
bilingual.target: 作为单身贵族，他享受自由的生活方式。

bilingual.source: Every citizen has the right to free speech.
bilingual.target: 每个公民都有言论自由的权利。

bilingual.source: Her heart is filled with a longing to be free.
bilingual.target: 她的心中充满了向往自由的渴望。

bilingual.source: In this free environment, he felt unconstrained.
bilingual.target: 在这个自由的环境中，他感到不受约束。

bilingual.source: He decided to become a ronin and live a free life.
bilingual.target: 他决定成为一名浪人，过自由的生活。

bilingual.source: Traveling gives him the joy of a longing to be free.
bilingual.target: 旅行让他感受到向往自由的快乐。

bilingual.source: No free man needs God; but was I free?
bilingual.target: 自由的人不需要上帝。但我是自由的吗？

bilingual.source: A free act of the will; free choices.
bilingual.target: 自愿的行动；自由的选择

list.abstract: free，英语单词，通常解释为“自由的、不受控制的”，做副词使用时意为“免费地、无约束地”，做动词使用时意为“使自由、解放”。
free，昵称灯哥、雷帝，韩国著名星际争霸职业选手。

yingyinNormal.en: If you want to be free, join us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你想成为一名自由的复制人就加入我们。

yingyinNormal.en: The hosts are the ones who are free. Free here under my control.
yingyinNormal.zh: 接待员才是自由的，在我的控制下，自由于此。

yingyinNormal.en: Her vision and ours will be realized. A free Panem. With self-determination for all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她和我们的目标终将实现，那将是一个自由的施惠国，人人独立自主。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know. Really? You think you could be happy here? Can anybody be happy if they aren't free?
yingyinNormal.zh: 说不准。真的吗？你认为在这里会幸福？没有自由的人会幸福吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Today, on the avenue of the tributes. All of Panem, a free Panem will watch more than a mere spectacle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天，在贡品大道上，所有自由的帕纳姆人民都将看到这一幕。

yingyinNormal.en: Private Doss, you are free to run into the hell fire of battle without a single weapon to protect yourself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 列兵多斯，你可自由的投入战斗的地狱烈火无需任何武器保护自己。

yingyinNormal.en: You know once we're in the air and the captain turns off the seat belt sign, you feel free to roam about my cabin.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我们升空，机长关闭系好安全带的标志后，你就可以自由的在我的小屋里遨游了。

yingyinNormal.en: You know the only place that voice left me alone? In my dreams. I was free. I could be as good or as bad as I felt like being.
yingyinNormal.zh: 知道我在哪儿才能躲开这个声音吗？在我的梦里，我是自由的，我是好是坏，多好多坏都随自己乐意。

yingyinNormal.en: The question of what it is to be an American, the very essence of American-ness, how we choose to lead our lives, open and free, is on the line.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作为美国人意味着什么，美国性的最核心本质，我们选择的开放自由的生活，这些都受到了威胁。

yingyinNormal.en: Really, what were you hoping for? I don't know, maybe that you'd be a little upset, and then you'd realize that I'm a stallion that has to run free. And that would turn you on a little.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是吗？那你期待的是什么反应？我也不知道，或许你会小小地生气一下，然后意识到我是一匹向往自由的骏马，这点会让你小小地性奋一下。

yingyinNormal.en: That's not true. Kindness is free. Love is free.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是真的，善良是免费的，爱也是。

yingyinNormal.en: Free calls. Free internet. For everyone. Forever.
yingyinNormal.zh: 免费电话，免费网络，人人共享，永久有效。

yingyinNormal.en: So do them for free.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你就做啊。

yingyinNormal.en: It's official. You're all free.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这次是正式的，你们都自由了。

yingyinNormal.en: Who's up for Sheldon-free Saturday?
yingyinNormal.zh: 谁同意周六来个无谢尔顿日？

yingyinNormal.en: I think... I think I want to be free.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得，我觉得我想获得自由。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. This guy just wants a free lunch.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，这家伙就是想来一顿免费的午餐。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water》

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, look. And we get these free T-shirts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有免费T恤拿。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean why wouldn't you get things for free?
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么不去买免费的呢？

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Fishbein, I'm sorry, but it's free speech.
yingyinNormal.zh: 费斯本先生，我很抱歉，但这是言论自由。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: Likewise, automation should eventually boost productivity, stimulate demand by driving down prices, and <highlight>free</highlight> workers from hard, boring work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同样，自动化最终应该会提高生产率，通过压低价格刺激需求，将工人从繁重、枯燥的工作中解放出来。

examination_example.sentence: This is not a <highlight>free</highlight> market but a biased one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这不是一个自由市场，而是一个有偏见的市场。

examination_example.sentence: They gave justices permanent positions so they would be <highlight>free</highlight> to upset those in power and have no need to cultivate political support.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们给予法官们终身任期，以便法官们能自由地推翻当权者，且无需拉拢政治支持。

examination_example.sentence: Other scientists perform the specialised work of peer review also for <highlight>free</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他科学家也免费进行同行评议的专业工作。

examination_example.sentence: With the content of papers secured for <highlight>free</highlight>, the publisher needs only find a market for its journal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 坐拥免费得来的论文，出版商只需要为期刊打开销路即可。

examination_example.sentence: Events are <highlight>free</highlight>, staffed by thousands of volunteers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些活动是免费的，有成千上万的志愿者。

examination_example.sentence: He <highlight>freed</highlight> music from hitherto prevailing conventions of harmony and structure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他打破了迄今为止还在盛行的乐曲要遵从和声结构的常规惯例。

sense_info_list.en: not doing anything planned or important, or available to be used
sense_info_list.zh: 空闲的; 未被占用的

examination_example.sentence: People use their <highlight>free</highlight> time to counterbalance the intellectual and emotional demands of their jobs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们利用空闲时间来平衡工作对智力和情感的要求。

examination_example.sentence: Kid’s use of screens may give their parents some <highlight>free</highlight> time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子使用电子产品可能会给他们的父母一些空闲时间。

examination_example.sentence: Some imagine that the coming work-<highlight>free</highlight> world will be defined by inequality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些人认为，未来的无工作世界将被不平等定义。

examination_example.sentence: find wildfire-<highlight>free</highlight> parts of the landscape
examination_example.sentence_trans: 寻找没有火灾的地方

examination_example.sentence: But in my experience, using such methods to <highlight>free</highlight> up the odd 30 minutes doesn't work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但在我看来，使用这些方法来腾出个30分钟左右的阅读时间是不管用的。

sense_info_list.en: (of a literary style) not observing the strict laws of form

examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果是的话，你可以很容易地把它退回给制造商，他们肯定会免费送你一个全新的。

examination_example.sentence: And the most valuable kind of homework for elementary level children was simply assigned <highlight>free</highlight> reading.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对小学水平的孩子来说，最有价值的家庭作业就是指定自由阅读。

examination_example.sentence: Unburdening yourself of frustration and perhaps even anger to someone who isn't a friend or close colleague can be wonderfully <highlight>freeing</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 向不是朋友或亲密同事的人倾诉自己的沮丧甚至愤怒，这是一种很棒的释放。

examination_example.sentence: This would allow the casual user to save money and time, <highlight>freeing</highlight> up casual space in our busy lives to read a good book.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这将使休闲用户节省金钱和时间，从而在忙碌的生活中腾出休闲空间来阅读一本好书。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管事实上所有的牛奶都天然不含转基因成分，但这是另一个对食物产生不必要恐惧的标签。

free作“摆脱…的”“大方的”时，只用作表语。
示例：This service is free of charge.
该服务是免费的。

examination_example.sentence: Almost half the center of Paris will be accessible only by foot or bicycle this Sunday to mark World Car-<highlight>Free</highlight> Day.

examination_example.sentence: What motivated the mayor of Paris to promote the first World Car-<highlight>Free</highlight> Day in her city?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 是什么促使巴黎市长在城市推广第一个世界无车日?

examination_example.sentence: What will happen on World Car-<highlight>Free</highlight> Day in Paris?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在巴黎的世界无车日将会发生什么?

examination_example.sentence: They spent six hours a day writing text messages, on social media, and online during their <highlight>free</highlight> time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们在空闲时间每天花6个小时写短信、上社交媒体和上网。

examination_example.sentence: Are you <highlight>free</highlight> to come over for a coffee early next week?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 下周初你有空过来喝杯咖啡吗？

examination_example.sentence: So if any of you have some <highlight>free</highlight> time during the weekend, please come join us at ReBicycle.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以如果你在周末有空闲时间，请加入我们ReBicycle。

examination_example.sentence: Given 15 minutes of <highlight>free</highlight> play, four- and five-year-olds will spend a third of this time engaged in spatial activities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 给4到5岁的孩子15分钟的自由玩耍时间，他们将花三分之一的时间从事空间活动。

examination_example.sentence: Pedestrians will have <highlight>free</highlight> access to the city.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 行人可以自由进出这座城市。

examination_example.sentence: The focus on academic "skills and drills" has cut deeply into recess and other time for <highlight>free</highlight> play.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 专注于学术“技能训练”已经减少深入休会和其他自由发挥的时间。

examination_example.sentence: Staff members hold plenty of bar events for guests like <highlight>free</highlight> shots, bar crawls and karaoke.

examination_example.sentence: How many people can each grand prize winner take on the <highlight>free</highlight> trip?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每个大奖得主可以带多少人参加免费旅行？

examination_example.sentence: Many lessons are now available online, from which students can choose for <highlight>free</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多课程现在都可以在网上获得，学生可以从中免费选择。

examination_example.sentence: Young children need more <highlight>free</highlight> time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 小孩子需要更多的自由时间。

examination_example.sentence: Then, Larry asked the police if he was needed or <highlight>free</highlight> to go.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后，拉里问警察是否需要他或者他可以走了。

examination_example.sentence: At one time, I even felt my parents couldn't understand me so I hoped I could be <highlight>free</highlight> from them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有一段时间，我甚至觉得我的父母不能理解我，所以我希望我能摆脱他们。

examination_example.sentence: When people see you trying to be funny, it <highlight>frees</highlight> them to try it themselves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当人们看到你试图搞笑的时候，他们就有自由去尝试。

examination_example.sentence: So even if your own efforts at humor fall short, you might be <highlight>freeing</highlight> the long kept humor in others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因此，即使你自己在幽默方面的努力没有达到预期效果，你也可能在释放别人长期以来的幽默感。

examination_example.sentence: His words <highlight>freed</highlight> me from my bad dreams.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的话使我从噩梦中解脱出来。

examination_example.sentence: Mr. Stone is <highlight>free</highlight> this afternoon after 3:00.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 斯通先生今天下午三点后有空。

examination_example.sentence: Once I had a boy who worked experimentally with Tinkertoys in his <highlight>free</highlight> time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有一次，我有一个男孩，他在空闲时间和小叮当一起做实验。

examination_example.sentence: He offered to fix bikes <highlight>free</highlight> of charge for anyone who needed it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他提出为任何需要的人免费修理自行车。

examination_example.sentence: He also asked for unwanted bikes, which he would repair—again for <highlight>free</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他还寻求没人要的自行车，他会修理——同样是免费的。

examination_example.sentence: Well, uh…about fifteen dollars an hour, five hours a day, and Sunday <highlight>free</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 嗯，嗯……大约一小时十五美元，一天五小时，星期天免费。

examination_example.sentence: Quality counts less than attitude and effort-even stupid joke can relieve/<highlight>free</highlight> others of risk and embarrassment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 质量比态度和努力更重要——即使是愚蠢的笑话也能减轻/消除他人的风险和尴尬。
